gomodel:SYNGO_1041  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Much signal was detected outside synapses (\"unclassified processes\" FIg1B). Fig1 C shows presynaptic DAB labeling of Flotilin-1 in parietal cortex. Of 50 Flot1 positive synapses, 80% of the signals was on the presynaptic side, the remainder on the postsynaptic side (main text p85). This is in line with qualitative observations in the visual cortex of rats (PMID 25732136, Fig6 see additional reference).\n\n8/7/2017 Pim\n- Authors note: \"In synapses, one or two patchy areas appeared on perisynaptic membranes, axon terminals, but never on presynaptic active zones or postsynaptic densities (Fig. 1C), although about half of the synapses showed no labeling\". Experimental description: M&M: \"Adult female Wistar rats, 10 weeks old, were used for this study\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5259-4945" ;
        dc:date           "2017-08-07" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1041" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

